Sentencas: The effects of Ca and Zn substitution, respectively, for Y and Co in (Y1-xCax)BaCo4-yZnyO7 (0.25 <= x <= 0.75 and 1.0 <= y <= 1.75) on the structure, high-temperature phase stability, thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), and electrochemical performance for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC) have been investigated.
Titulo: Characterization of (Y1-xCax)BaCo4-yZnyO7 as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The (Y1-xCax)BaCo4-yZnyO7 oxides crystallize in a trigonal P31c symmetry similar to YBaCo4O7.
Titulo: Characterization of (Y1-xCax)BaCo4-yZnyO7 as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The substitution of Zn for Co improves the long-term phase stability at high temperatures, but at the expense of the electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Characterization of (Y1-xCax)BaCo4-yZnyO7 as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In contrast, the substitution of Ca for Y is improves electrochemical performances, but deteriorates the long-term phase stability at high temperatures at high Ca contents (x = 0.75 and 1.0).
Titulo: Characterization of (Y1-xCax)BaCo4-yZnyO7 as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among the various chemical compositions investigated in the (Y1-xCax)BaCo4-yZnyO7 system, the (Y0.5Ca0.5)BaCo2.5Zn1.5O7 composition offers a combination of good electrochemical performance and low TEC, while maintaining the phase stability at 600-800 degrees C for 120 h. The (Y0.5Ca0.5)BaCo2.5Zn1.5O7 + GDC (50: 50 wt. %) composite cathodes exhibit a maximum power density of similar to 450 mW cm(-2) at 700 degrees C in anode-supported single SOFC.
Titulo: Characterization of (Y1-xCax)BaCo4-yZnyO7 as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
